Actually, "p" means "progressive" as opposed to "i" which means interlaced. Progressive scanning is better than interlaced, as each frame uses every line of resolution where interlaced uses typically half the lines per frame. I note you always use progressive frames in your encodes ('cuz interlaced really only makes sense for some broadcast material, really).
